component.documentation:
The JSFConfigurationService service holds application configuration properties that are used at runtime. This service should not include properties that are needed at startup.
By default, default values are retrieved. However, these values can be overridden if specified in the nuxeo.conf file.
@since 7.4

extension-point.documentation:
The configuration extension point allows to define a set of properties. Each property can have a default value
specified.

Example:



    ${nuxeo.jsf.enableDoubleClickShield:=true}
    ${nuxeo.jsf.useAjaxTabs:=false}
    staticValue
